    "spiralJustification": "Jean-Paul Sartre's philosophical trajectory and political engagement strongly align with the Green stage of Spiral Dynamics. His existentialism, while rooted in radical individual freedom and autonomy (echoing Orange), fundamentally critiques rigid social structures, hierarchies, and pre-determined values, seeking authenticity and liberation from forms of 'bad faith' inherent in conformity or oppression. The Green stage emphasizes humanism, pluralism, social justice, and the search for meaning and community beyond conventional norms. Sartre's later synthesis with Marxism, anti-colonial activism, and critique of anti-Semitism exemplify a deep commitment to collective liberation and a relativistic/humanistic value system. His emphasis on dialogue, rejection of authoritarianism (including Soviet Communism), and fostering of 'group in fusion' dynamics reflect Green's search for harmonious, yet often conflictual, community grounded in shared humanity and freedom. While exhibiting traits of Orange (intellectual individualism, achievement) and gesturing towards Yellow (integrative synthesis of complex systems like existentialism and Marxism, reflexive critique of his own earlier positions), the core humanistic project of freedom, responsibility for the Other, and critique of oppression are most characteristic of the Green value system.",
